    "body": "Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated `library-new-request` job failed for `oracle.spectra.bundles:telemetry-jfr-mp-helidon:2607.0.8`.\n\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fjormundur00%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-7768-library-new-request-oracle.spectra.bundles-telemetry-jfr-mp-helidon-2607.0.8-d9cf6531\n\nThe most likely failing stage was after artifact discovery, when the workflow needed usable upstream source/test context for scaffold and test generation. `human-intervention-logs/oracle.spectra.bundles:telemetry-jfr-mp-helidon:2607.0.8/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log` shows the discovery step itself finished, but all repository lookups for this coordinate failed (`repo1.maven.org`, `repo.maven.apache.org`, and `maven.oracle.com/public` returned 404, and `search.maven.org` returned `numFound:0`). The generated `build/discovered-artifact-metadata/oracle.spectra.bundles-telemetry-jfr-mp-helidon-2607.0.8.json` was left with `repository-url`, `source-code-url`, `test-code-url`, and `documentation-url` all set to `N/A`, no target-specific files were generated under `tests/src`, `metadata`, or `stats` for this coordinate, and run metrics were unavailable.\n\nInspect `human-intervention-logs/oracle.spectra.bundles:telemetry-jfr-mp-helidon:2607.0.8/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log` first. If you still have the failed worktree locally, also inspect `build/agent-artifact-discovery-logs/oracle.spectra.bundles-telemetry-jfr-mp-helidon-2607.0.8.log` and `build/discovered-artifact-metadata/oracle.spectra.bundles-telemetry-jfr-mp-helidon-2607.0.8.json`.\n\n1. Verify where this artifact is actually published and manually identify valid repository, source, test, and documentation URLs if it is not available through Maven Central or the public Oracle Maven endpoints the job tried.\n2. Confirm that `telemetry-jfr-mp-helidon:2607.0.8` is a real JVM/native-image metadata target and identify the upstream sample or public API surface needed for a Helidon/JFR test.\n3. Once the upstream context is known, continue from the preserved branch or rerun the workflow with the corrected artifact metadata so scaffold and test generation can proceed.",
